The Assembly Committee, which is currently preparing the legislation introducing the change of name, has indicated that "the final decision on the name of the members of the Assembly falls to the members of the Assembly".
The Government of Wales Act of 2017 grants the Welsh Assembly the power to change its name.
In June, the Commission published the results of a public consultation on the proposal to designate the House as the Welsh Parliament, which was widely supported.
On the question of the title of members, the Commission favours members of the Welsh Parliament (or WMP); however, a vast majority of Welsh prefers MWP.
